A white Lamborghini Gallardo was extensively damaged after a truck collided into it on the R102 in the vicinity of Phoenix, north of Durban, on Saturday morning. According to the Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa), they were called out to the scene by passing motorists just after 8am in the morning. Rusa spokesperson, Prem Balram, said on arrival, the Lamborghini Gallardo was located on the right emergency lane. “It is alleged that a truck travelling next to the sports car suddenly veered into its lane resulting in the collision,” said Balram, adding that no injuries were reported.